Bibliographic References: PP, no. 121, pi. 22c; PPSupp, no. 165; PhV2 p. 41, no. 53 (with bibliography to date).
Imagery Description: (a) Phlyax with torch in 1. hand, carrying dish of cakes on his head, moving to 1. and looking back to r.; to 1., stele; to r., duck with worm in its mouth, (b) Dionysos, with drapery across legs, bending forward and holding a cista of eggs in his r. hand, thyrsus and wreath in 1.
